            7,
            [
                "1894,"
            ]
        ]
    ],
    "Methodologically, the book combined the English Arts-and-Crafts approach with a French rationalist tradition, derived from <a href=\"/choisya\">Auguste Choisy</a>\u00a0and his <em>L'art de b\u00e2tir chez les Byzantins</em> (Watkin).": [],
    "Between 1894 and 1918 he acted as Art Inspector to the Technical Education Board of the London County Council.": [],
    "He continued to design original work in various media, producing watercolors, and building structures in a non-historic (though medieval in mindset) until 1902.": [],
    "After that, his efforts were devoted to writing.": [],
    "In 1901 Lethaby was appointed professor of Design and Ornament at the Royal College of Art, a position he held until 1918.": [
